1 AN ACT concerning postsecondary education; relating to the state board
2 of regents; requiring postsecondary educational institutions to equip
3 certain pre-service teachers with essential knowledge and skills to
4 support children affected by fetal alcohol syndrome disorder.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. (a) The state board of regents and each postsecondary
8 educational institution shall ensure that pre-service teachers in the fields
9 of early childhood, elementary, secondary and special education, are
10 equipped with essential knowledge and skills to support children affected
11 by fetal alcohol syndrome disorder, including, but not limited to:
12 (1) The common signs of and behaviors associated with fetal alcohol
13 syndrome disorders;
14 (2) the impacts of fetal alcohol syndrome disorders upon learning and
15 behavior; and
16 (3) techniques for communicating with a parent or guardian about a
17 suspected fetal alcohol syndrome disorder, educational intervention efforts
18 and whether an evaluation for special education and related services is
19 warranted.
20 (b) As used in this section:
21 (1) "Pre-service teacher" means an individual who is receiving the
22 education and training to become a licensed teacher but is not yet licensed.
23 (2) "Postsecondary educational institution" means any:
24 (A) State educational institution as defined in K.S.A. 76-711, and
25 amendments thereto;
26 (B) municipal university;
27 (C) community college; or
28 (D) not-for-profit institution of postsecondary education that has its
29 main campus or principal place of operation in Kansas, is operated
30 independently and not controlled or administered by a state agency or
31 subdivision of this state, maintains open enrollment and is accredited by a
32 nationally recognized accrediting agency for higher education in the
33 United States.
34 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its

